label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 26: Algorismus
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Treatise on the fundamentals of arithmetic (Algorismus), followed by a treatise on cosmography that describes and illustrates the Ptolemaic model of a spherical earth divided into climactic zones at the center of the concentric spheres of the universe. The second treatise has marginal notes in the same ink and possibly hand as the text, as well as notes in a later cursive hand in faint ink and a bifolium written in this later hand bound in (f. 23-24).
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: 
        Layout: Written in 25-26 lines; prickings visible on many leaves.
        Script: Written in Gothic script.
        Decoration: 7 astronomical diagrams in black and red ink (f. 10r, 12r, 12v, 25v, 28r, 28v, 29r), 2 astronomical diagrams in black ink (f. 29v, 30r), and 2 illustrations in red and black ink (f. 13r), all in second work; 2-line initial in red and blue with faded penwork extensions (f. 1r); 5-line divided initial in red (f. 9v); caption title (f. 1r) and marginal rubrics in first work (f. 1r-9v) in red, 2-line initials and paragraph marks throughout in red.
        Binding: 20th-century morocco with gilt (rebound in 1997).
        Origin: Written in Italy in the mid-13th century.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 26
